 forgotten this.<br>
<br>
She heard Yakut speaking about myrrh and sweetgrass, Sinope,who was a warrior-priestess and liking incense burning to honor Artemis had brought some  myrrh from Carthage.And her aunt Artaisha, who is a priestess of Artemis in Ephesus had given her a pouch of sweetgrass.She told to the Shamaness:<br>
<br>
&quot;Thanks the All Mother!...the Ancients( she was remembering that the Northern Amazons weren't worshipping the gods and goddesses) I recently returned from Carthage and brought with me myrrh that I wanted to burn as incense for Artemis .For the same purpose, my aunt gave me a pouch of sweetgrass that I still keep in my hut. Stay with her, I'll return as quick as I can&quot;<br>
<br>
Sinope got to her hut, took the myrrh and her pouch of sweetgrass and brought them to Yakut. She arrived as quick as a tempest.<br>
<br>
&quot; I hope it can heal her, thanks for your help, do you need anything else,I feel I 'll never be grateful enough. What do you think it is, I hope she hadn't been...poisoned&quot; She spoke the last word with a broken voice, worried.<br>
<br>
<br>
Holding Sheyala's hand, she told her, begging her to survive:<br>
<br>
&quot; Please hold on, fight for your life, I care for you, I couldn't live without you, we all do. Hold on, for our tribe, for our Nation, for all those who love you, for me...&quot;<br>
<br>
A tear flew on her cheek, but she soon retook courage. As hope was living in her heart.<br>
<br>
